WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:02.090 --> 00:00:03.633
<i>Previously on</i> Lost:

2
00:00:03.717 --> 00:00:05.218
You brought me to operate.

3
00:00:05.302 --> 00:00:08.346
You think I trust you.
that I'm gonna just do the surgery

4
00:00:08.430 --> 00:00:10.348
and hope that you let me go?

5
00:00:10.432 --> 00:00:13.768
Jack... you have to do it.

6
00:00:13.935 --> 00:00:16.521
How did they get you to ask me?
What did they offer?

7
00:00:16.605 --> 00:00:18.106
- Nothing!
- Why are you here?

8
00:00:18.190 --> 00:00:20.066
They're gonna kill Sawyer!

9
00:00:26.448 --> 00:00:28.200
Tomorrow morning. first thing.

10
00:00:28.283 --> 00:00:30.535
I'll get it out.
and I'll keep you alive.

11
00:00:32.954 --> 00:00:34.289
I'm ready.

12
00:00:34.873 --> 00:00:38.126
No! No! Sawyer. please!

13
00:00:38.251 --> 00:00:40.045
You get your hands off of him!

14
00:00:42.589 --> 00:00:45.008
I made a small incision
in Ben's kidney sack.

15
00:00:45.717 --> 00:00:49.012
Now. if I don't stitch that back up
in the next hour. he's dead.

16
00:00:49.095 --> 00:00:51.723
Now get in here
and bring that walkie-talkie!

17
00:00:53.000 --> 00:00:59.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

18
00:01:39.104 --> 00:01:40.438
Hello.

19
00:02:24.983 --> 00:02:26.318
I fell asleep?

20
00:02:26.401 --> 00:02:29.237
With candles burning.
That's real safe.

21
00:02:34.701 --> 00:02:36.870
We don't have to
keep doing this. you know.

22
00:02:37.662 --> 00:02:41.458
Are you saying that because
you don't think it's gonna work?

23
00:02:41.541 --> 00:02:43.752
Or because you're afraid
he'll find out?

24
00:02:47.714 --> 00:02:49.632
Lift up your shirt.

25
00:03:06.816 --> 00:03:08.068
OK.

26
00:03:10.570 --> 00:03:13.490
- Some doctor you are.
- I'm not doing this as your doctor.

27
00:03:13.573 --> 00:03:15.450
I'm doing it as your sister.

28
00:03:18.119 --> 00:03:20.038
I don't like you being here alone.

29
00:03:20.121 --> 00:03:21.706
Come stay with me.

30
00:03:21.790 --> 00:03:24.793
I like living on the beach.

31
00:03:24.876 --> 00:03:27.712
This is Miami. Rachel.

32
00:03:27.796 --> 00:03:29.964
Everything's on the beach.

33
00:03:36.554 --> 00:03:38.848
You have an hour head start.

34
00:03:38.932 --> 00:03:40.642
Take the walkie. take Sawyer. go.

35
00:03:40.809 --> 00:03:42.143
<i>Wait. where are you?</i>

36
00:03:42.227 --> 00:03:45.814
Kate. just listen to me! Do you
remember what I told you on the beach?

37
00:03:45.897 --> 00:03:49.359
Do you remember what story I told you
when you were stitching me up?

38
00:03:50.151 --> 00:03:53.405
- Do you remember it?
- Yes! Yes! I remember!

39
00:03:54.406 --> 00:03:58.368
When you get safe.
you radio me and you tell me that story.

40
00:03:58.451 --> 00:03:59.494
<i>Jack. please...</i>

41
00:03:59.577 --> 00:04:03.206
If you don't call in an hour. I'll know
something went wrong and he dies!

42
00:04:03.498 --> 00:04:06.084
<i>- I can't leave without you!</i>
- Yes. you are. Go.

43
00:04:06.167 --> 00:04:08.253
- Jack. I can't!
- Go! Now!

44
00:04:08.336 --> 00:04:11.256
- I can't!
- Kate! Damn it! Run!

45
00:04:16.469 --> 00:04:19.264
Juliet. stop the bleeding
and stitch him up.

46
00:04:19.597 --> 00:04:21.683
She's not a surgeon.
She can't fix this.

47
00:04:24.185 --> 00:04:25.520
He's right.

48
00:04:34.696 --> 00:04:35.947
Let's go.

49
00:04:38.283 --> 00:04:40.869
<i>- Warning.</i>
- Sawyer. let's go!

50
00:04:40.994 --> 00:04:42.120
<i>- Warning.</i>
- Sawyer!

51
00:04:54.382 --> 00:04:57.635
Then what the hell
do you suggest we do?

52
00:04:59.345 --> 00:05:03.183
Go get Danny.
then find Austen and Ford

53
00:05:03.266 --> 00:05:04.476
and bring them back.

54
00:05:04.559 --> 00:05:07.228
No. You do that and Ben dies.

55
00:05:07.312 --> 00:05:09.564
- Go.
- No. you think I'm lying?

56
00:05:09.647 --> 00:05:12.400
You think this is a bluff?
I will let him die.

57
00:05:12.484 --> 00:05:14.068
No. Jack. You won't.

58
00:05:16.154 --> 00:05:18.615
Go. Get them back.

59
00:05:19.491 --> 00:05:21.534
If you have to...

60
00:05:22.744 --> 00:05:24.037
...kill them.

61
00:06:03.743 --> 00:06:05.286
- Hello?
<i>- Dr. Burke?</i>

62
00:06:05.370 --> 00:06:08.122
- Yes.
<i>- It's Diana from Mittelos BioScience.</i>

63
00:06:08.248 --> 00:06:11.042
<i>- Confirming your appointment tomorrow.</i>
- 2:00. right?

64
00:06:11.125 --> 00:06:14.921
<i>2:00. Dr. Alpert asked me to tell you
he's looking forward to meeting you.</i>

65
00:06:15.004 --> 00:06:17.131
- Me. too. Thank you.
<i>- Goodbye.</i>

66
00:07:09.350 --> 00:07:10.727
Stay here.

67
00:07:15.440 --> 00:07:18.526
- Hello. Juliet.
- Hey.

68
00:07:21.362 --> 00:07:23.114
Hey. Ed.

69
00:07:25.575 --> 00:07:27.410
Why exactly are you here?

70
00:07:27.493 --> 00:07:30.496
Oh. I. um... today's lab work.

71
00:07:30.580 --> 00:07:34.250
I got home and I realized
that I inverted some numbers.

72
00:07:34.334 --> 00:07:36.127
It couldn't wait until morning?

73
00:07:38.379 --> 00:07:41.716
- Edmund?
- I'm sorry.

74
00:07:42.050 --> 00:07:43.259
How rude of me.

75
00:07:43.343 --> 00:07:46.721
Juliet. this is Sherry.
Sherry. this is Juliet...

76
00:07:47.096 --> 00:07:49.140
...my ex-wife.

77
00:07:52.060 --> 00:07:53.561
Juliet's leaving.

78
00:07:55.772 --> 00:07:57.190
I am.

79
00:07:59.734 --> 00:08:01.569
Jules...

80
00:08:02.403 --> 00:08:05.740
...could you please turn off the lights?

81
00:08:17.585 --> 00:08:20.880
You haven't thought this through.
Your plan's not going to work.

82
00:08:20.963 --> 00:08:22.590
Yeah? Why's that?

83
00:08:22.674 --> 00:08:26.469
Your friends won't make it to your side.
because we're not on that island.

84
00:08:28.346 --> 00:08:30.973
We're on a smaller island.
two miles off shore.

85
00:08:33.101 --> 00:08:34.769
Afraid so.

86
00:08:39.607 --> 00:08:43.945
So. why don't we see if we can come up
with some kind of peaceful resolution.

87
00:08:46.531 --> 00:08:48.825
- A peaceful resolution?
- That's right.

88
00:08:48.908 --> 00:08:52.620
Is that what you call asking me to kill
Ben while on the operating table?

89
00:08:52.745 --> 00:08:55.331
- "Make it look like an accident?"
- Ridiculous.

90
00:08:55.415 --> 00:08:58.918
- What are you trying to do. Jack?
- She said if I did. she'd protect me!

91
00:08:59.001 --> 00:09:00.545
Enough!

92
00:09:03.464 --> 00:09:06.342
Juliet. get out.

93
00:09:07.385 --> 00:09:10.638
- Tom. he's lying!
- You said you can't stitch him up?

94
00:09:10.805 --> 00:09:13.599
Then you don't need to be in here.

95
00:09:13.683 --> 00:09:14.809
Go. Julie.

96
00:09:22.233 --> 00:09:24.235
Don't let him fool you.

97
00:09:24.318 --> 00:09:26.904
He'll never let a patient just die.

98
00:09:31.659 --> 00:09:33.077
Hey!

99
00:09:33.161 --> 00:09:35.371
Hey! Can anybody hear me?

100
00:09:38.124 --> 00:09:40.334
- What happened?
- Open the cage!

101
00:09:40.418 --> 00:09:43.004
- Where's...
- Just open the damn cage!

102
00:10:01.981 --> 00:10:03.649
That's our island?

103
00:10:03.733 --> 00:10:05.526
You didn't believe me before?

104
00:10:05.610 --> 00:10:06.778
We need a boat.

105
00:10:06.861 --> 00:10:08.946
And a couple of towels
and a buffet lunch.

106
00:10:09.030 --> 00:10:11.532
We'll follow the beach.
There's got to be one.

107
00:10:11.657 --> 00:10:13.576
How else do they get back and forth?

108
00:10:13.659 --> 00:10:16.746
Well. why don't we just
stop and ask for directions?

109
00:10:19.457 --> 00:10:21.793
<i>- Jack. are you there?</i>
- Yeah.

110
00:10:21.876 --> 00:10:23.628
<i>- Yeah. I'm here.</i>
- Are you OK?

111
00:10:23.711 --> 00:10:26.130
<i>- I'm fine.</i>
- Tell him I said hi. Get to the point!

112
00:10:26.214 --> 00:10:29.759
Jack. we need a boat. We need
some way to get off of this island.

113
00:10:30.718 --> 00:10:32.845
You heard her.

114
00:10:32.929 --> 00:10:34.889
How do they get off this island?

115
00:10:36.891 --> 00:10:38.434
What's he doing?

116
00:10:38.518 --> 00:10:39.685
Kate? Kate!

117
00:10:44.357 --> 00:10:45.691
Kate!

118
00:10:50.238 --> 00:10:51.489
Come on!

119
00:11:02.875 --> 00:11:04.752
Come on! Go! Go. go!

120
00:11:35.658 --> 00:11:37.243
This way!

121
00:11:38.327 --> 00:11:39.996
Jason. you all right?

122
00:11:42.915 --> 00:11:44.166
They're over there!

123
00:11:53.384 --> 00:11:56.137
Come on! Get inside! Get inside! Go!

124
00:12:01.142 --> 00:12:02.852
Come on!

125
00:12:06.439 --> 00:12:08.524
Be quiet. be quiet. be quiet!

126
00:12:10.818 --> 00:12:12.153
Sh. shh.

127
00:12:12.236 --> 00:12:13.362
Be quiet...

128
00:12:14.864 --> 00:12:16.407
Where'd they go?

129
00:12:16.490 --> 00:12:17.950
That way.

130
00:12:28.127 --> 00:12:30.004
Nice to meet you. Sheena.

131
00:12:31.422 --> 00:12:33.925
Is it true?

132
00:12:34.008 --> 00:12:36.344
- Is what true?
- What you said.

133
00:12:37.345 --> 00:12:39.847
Did Juliet really ask you to kill him?

134
00:12:41.891 --> 00:12:45.603
Yeah. and in about 40 minutes.
she's gonna get her wish.

135
00:12:45.686 --> 00:12:47.063
Hey...

136
00:12:52.818 --> 00:12:56.072
That's not helping...

137
00:12:56.989 --> 00:12:58.407
...anything.

138
00:13:02.662 --> 00:13:04.705
Now...

139
00:13:05.373 --> 00:13:08.876
...could somebody please get Juliet?

140
00:13:18.886 --> 00:13:20.513
Juliet?

141
00:13:21.347 --> 00:13:23.432
Edmund wants to see you in his office.

142
00:13:25.184 --> 00:13:27.144
Do you work here?

143
00:13:27.228 --> 00:13:29.355
I'm the new research assistant.

144
00:13:31.148 --> 00:13:33.150
Of course you are.

145
00:13:48.457 --> 00:13:50.042
I want in.

146
00:13:51.544 --> 00:13:54.922
- In on what?
- I know what you're doing. Juliet.

147
00:13:57.174 --> 00:14:00.136
- I'm not really sure what you...
- I read your notes.

148
00:14:00.970 --> 00:14:02.680
I know what you took from the lab.

149
00:14:02.763 --> 00:14:04.473
The only thing I don't know is...

150
00:14:05.808 --> 00:14:07.518
...who's your guinea pig?

151
00:14:10.271 --> 00:14:11.939
Ed. I've...

152
00:14:12.023 --> 00:14:16.235
I've been doing my research
in my own lab on my own time.

153
00:14:16.318 --> 00:14:19.196
- I don't really see how...
- It's your sister. isn't it?

154
00:14:21.365 --> 00:14:24.869
Look. Jules. there's two ways
this plays out.

155
00:14:26.120 --> 00:14:30.332
One is your research is potentially...

156
00:14:30.416 --> 00:14:31.792
...genius.

157
00:14:33.127 --> 00:14:34.503
And the other...

158
00:14:35.212 --> 00:14:38.799
...it raises some very
serious ethical questions.

159
00:14:39.633 --> 00:14:42.303
Maybe even criminal concerns.

160
00:14:43.554 --> 00:14:45.973
But if you collaborate with me...

161
00:14:47.725 --> 00:14:50.644
...based on my reputation.

162
00:14:50.728 --> 00:14:54.815
all this is viewed
as cutting-edge science.

163
00:14:55.149 --> 00:14:59.904
And we will win prizes
and drink champagne...

164
00:15:01.405 --> 00:15:03.783
...and do a lot of good for people.

165
00:15:13.667 --> 00:15:16.003
Why don't I give you time
to think about it?

166
00:15:33.062 --> 00:15:34.438
Juliet.

167
00:15:37.024 --> 00:15:38.526
Ben's awake.

168
00:15:40.319 --> 00:15:41.403
How?

169
00:15:41.779 --> 00:15:46.325
Shephard says he's a spinal surgeon.
not an anesthesiologist.

170
00:15:47.827 --> 00:15:49.912
Ben's asking for you.

171
00:15:59.255 --> 00:16:02.550
This a hobby of yours. Underdog.
digging holes?

172
00:16:02.633 --> 00:16:06.095
Yep. That and basket weaving.
Want one?

173
00:16:08.264 --> 00:16:11.600
- Have a tunnel to the mainland?
- No. but I've got a boat.

174
00:16:13.394 --> 00:16:15.521
- Can we use it?
- Yeah.

175
00:16:15.604 --> 00:16:18.232
- But we've got to hurry.
- Hold on a second. sister.

176
00:16:18.315 --> 00:16:20.734
You happen to find us
in the woods. you have a boat

177
00:16:20.901 --> 00:16:22.903
and you're gonna let us use it?

178
00:16:24.363 --> 00:16:27.074
- There's something we need to do first.
- Oh. gee.

179
00:16:27.199 --> 00:16:29.577
My boyfriend is being held prisoner.

180
00:16:29.702 --> 00:16:33.497
If you help me rescue him. I promise
I'll get you back to the other island.

181
00:16:34.039 --> 00:16:36.000
Your boyfriend.

182
00:16:36.083 --> 00:16:38.586
his name happen to be "Karl?"

183
00:16:40.713 --> 00:16:42.548
Yeah.

184
00:16:43.591 --> 00:16:45.217
Come on.

185
00:16:49.096 --> 00:16:53.350
- I stopped the surgery.
- I know.

186
00:16:53.434 --> 00:16:56.937
I've been able to hear you
for a few minutes now.

187
00:16:57.688 --> 00:17:00.274
It's very clever of you.

188
00:17:00.357 --> 00:17:02.276
I should have seen it coming.

189
00:17:04.778 --> 00:17:07.448
- Are you in pain? I can...
- No.

190
00:17:08.616 --> 00:17:10.701
But thanks all the same.

191
00:17:24.131 --> 00:17:27.676
I'd like to speak to Juliet alone.
please. Jack.

192
00:17:27.801 --> 00:17:29.386
No. no. I'm sorry.

193
00:17:29.470 --> 00:17:32.973
Please. I'm asking you.

194
00:17:33.057 --> 00:17:35.893
One gentleman to another.

195
00:17:36.936 --> 00:17:40.397
It won't hurt you to give me
three minutes. will it?

196
00:17:41.982 --> 00:17:45.402
Knowing I have only 27 left.

197
00:17:58.791 --> 00:18:01.293
- If you touch him. if you try to...
- I won't.

198
00:18:06.090 --> 00:18:07.675
You've got three minutes.

199
00:18:32.032 --> 00:18:33.534
I'm Tom. by the way.

200
00:18:54.513 --> 00:18:56.640
They've got history.

201
00:19:14.700 --> 00:19:16.827
I would like for you
to go back in there.

202
00:19:16.910 --> 00:19:19.330
put Ben under and finish the surgery.

203
00:19:21.749 --> 00:19:24.418
And why would I wanna do that?

204
00:19:24.501 --> 00:19:27.254
Because I'm going to go
help your friends escape.

205
00:19:39.099 --> 00:19:42.811
Thank you for taking the time
to let us make our pitch. Dr. Burke.

206
00:19:42.936 --> 00:19:47.358
Mittelos BioScience is based in Oregon.
we're just outside of Portland.

207
00:19:51.362 --> 00:19:55.532
These shots might seem cheeseball.
but our people really are this happy.

208
00:19:55.616 --> 00:20:00.204
Now. why? Because we're privately
funded. Privately funded means freedom.

209
00:20:03.415 --> 00:20:06.668
We organize trips every week
in and around the Portland area.

210
00:20:06.752 --> 00:20:11.131
which is just awesome for hiking.
and biking. and river running.

211
00:20:13.300 --> 00:20:17.971
Look. when your company
reached out to me. I was flattered.

212
00:20:18.055 --> 00:20:20.391
but I don't really know why
you would want me.

213
00:20:20.474 --> 00:20:24.853
Is it true that you successfully
impregnated a male field mouse?

214
00:20:26.397 --> 00:20:28.732
Well. he didn't carry to term.

215
00:20:29.817 --> 00:20:32.653
- You mind if I ask you something?
- Sure.

216
00:20:36.907 --> 00:20:38.784
What do you see?

217
00:20:40.619 --> 00:20:43.831
Well... it's a human womb. obviously.

218
00:20:44.415 --> 00:20:49.044
Judging from the decomposition of the
endometrium. I'd say the woman was 70.

219
00:20:49.128 --> 00:20:53.424
- Actually. she's 26.
- What happened to her?

220
00:20:53.507 --> 00:20:57.511
What if I told you that you could have
complete freedom and money to find out?

221
00:20:59.388 --> 00:21:02.015
We think you're special. Dr. Burke.

222
00:21:02.099 --> 00:21:04.643
We want you to lead a team
of highly trained people

223
00:21:04.726 --> 00:21:07.062
because we think
you're just that good.

224
00:21:07.729 --> 00:21:09.523
I can't.

225
00:21:10.190 --> 00:21:12.109
Why can't you?

226
00:21:12.192 --> 00:21:14.278
My ex-husband wouldn't let me.

227
00:21:14.361 --> 00:21:17.197
- He wouldn't give you this opportunity?
- No.

228
00:21:17.322 --> 00:21:19.199
He would never give the OK.

229
00:21:19.283 --> 00:21:21.702
- We could reach out to him.
- Don't bother.

230
00:21:21.785 --> 00:21:25.706
- Must be something he'd respond to.
- If he were hit by a bus.

231
00:21:25.789 --> 00:21:27.040
That would work.

232
00:21:30.836 --> 00:21:33.005
- That was totally inappropriate.
- No.

233
00:21:36.008 --> 00:21:38.260
I'm sorry that I wasted your time.

234
00:21:38.969 --> 00:21:41.430
- Dr. Burke. please. you...
- No. I'm sorry.

235
00:21:42.222 --> 00:21:45.058
Whatever you think I am. I'm not.

236
00:21:45.934 --> 00:21:48.604
I'm not a leader. Mr. Alpert.

237
00:21:49.271 --> 00:21:51.106
I'm a mess.

238
00:22:34.691 --> 00:22:36.485
Oh. hell.

239
00:22:47.538 --> 00:22:49.540
Karl's gotta be in there.

240
00:22:49.623 --> 00:22:51.625
What. you mean you ain't sure?

241
00:22:52.084 --> 00:22:54.211
It's the only place I haven't looked.

242
00:22:54.294 --> 00:22:57.047
- You know the guard?
- Yeah.

243
00:22:57.130 --> 00:23:00.175
- His name's Aldo.
- "Aldo?"

244
00:23:01.385 --> 00:23:05.973
OK. Lollipop. tell me how we're gonna
get by him with one gun and no bullets?

245
00:23:06.056 --> 00:23:07.975
I've got an idea.

246
00:23:08.767 --> 00:23:10.310
Of course you do.

247
00:23:12.062 --> 00:23:14.481
- Open the door!
- Alex?

248
00:23:14.565 --> 00:23:16.024
What the hell are you doing?

249
00:23:16.108 --> 00:23:19.820
They got out of their cages! I caught
them in the jungle. Now open up!

250
00:23:19.903 --> 00:23:24.157
Just stop! You're not supposed to be
here. Your dad's gonna kill you!

251
00:23:24.241 --> 00:23:27.995
My dad was the one who told me
to bring them here. to you.

252
00:23:28.078 --> 00:23:32.416
Look. maybe you should call him.
I'm sure he's got nothing better to do.

253
00:23:39.840 --> 00:23:44.595
- Danny. I need Ben.
<i>- Why?</i>

254
00:23:44.678 --> 00:23:47.598
I got Alex here. she's got
Austen and Ford with her...

255
00:23:49.516 --> 00:23:51.852
<i>Damn it! Whatever she says
don't believe it!</i>

256
00:23:51.935 --> 00:23:54.146
<i>You hold them right there.
I'm on my...</i>

257
00:23:54.938 --> 00:23:59.401
Don't get mad at me because you fell
for the old Wookiee Prisoner gag.

258
00:23:59.943 --> 00:24:02.863
- Where's Karl?
- What are you talking about?

259
00:24:02.946 --> 00:24:04.990
Shoot him in the knee.

260
00:24:05.866 --> 00:24:08.368
- What?
- We don't have time. I'll do it.

261
00:24:10.829 --> 00:24:14.541
OK! All right! He's at the end of the
hall! Room 23! Keys are in my pocket!

262
00:24:21.548 --> 00:24:24.176
Good con. I almost believed
you were gonna shoot him.

263
00:24:24.259 --> 00:24:25.719
It wasn't a con.

264
00:24:26.720 --> 00:24:27.929
Here it is!

265
00:24:29.931 --> 00:24:32.100
I ain't feeling this.

266
00:25:35.539 --> 00:25:36.623
Help!

267
00:25:37.082 --> 00:25:38.208
Help!

268
00:25:46.675 --> 00:25:49.177
You're OK. You're OK. Karl.

269
00:26:00.647 --> 00:26:01.690
Is he OK?

270
00:26:01.815 --> 00:26:04.568
We got your boyfriend back.
Where's your damn boat?

271
00:26:11.366 --> 00:26:13.410
Idiot.

272
00:26:13.493 --> 00:26:16.163
- Where are they?
- I don't know. Alex was with them.

273
00:26:16.246 --> 00:26:18.081
Danny!

274
00:26:19.666 --> 00:26:21.001
We're letting them go.

275
00:26:21.126 --> 00:26:23.295
- Letting 'em go?
- Ben gave the order.

276
00:26:23.378 --> 00:26:25.380
- Ben's in surgery.
- He woke up.

277
00:26:25.464 --> 00:26:27.674
- He woke up. huh?
- Shephard won't do the surgery

278
00:26:27.841 --> 00:26:32.137
unless he knows his friends are off
the island. Do you want Ben to die?

279
00:26:32.220 --> 00:26:35.557
I know Ben would rather die
than let them go!

280
00:26:49.654 --> 00:26:51.198
Hey.

281
00:26:52.324 --> 00:26:53.867
How was the interview?

282
00:26:55.368 --> 00:26:57.078
It's not for me.

283
00:26:57.412 --> 00:26:59.539
- What?
- It's fine.

284
00:26:59.623 --> 00:27:02.334
They're too far away anyway.
It's Portland.

285
00:27:02.417 --> 00:27:06.546
- You didn't say no because of me?
- Why would I want to go to Portland

286
00:27:06.630 --> 00:27:08.757
for research that doesn't even work?

287
00:27:10.675 --> 00:27:12.552
Because it does work.

288
00:27:19.142 --> 00:27:20.894
I'm pregnant.

289
00:27:25.065 --> 00:27:27.067
I'm p... I'm pregnant.

290
00:27:28.568 --> 00:27:31.363
- What?
- Look. look...

291
00:27:31.446 --> 00:27:33.031
I took a blood test. too.

292
00:27:33.114 --> 00:27:35.283
I didn't want to tell you
till I was sure.

293
00:27:38.662 --> 00:27:40.580
- It worked.
- Yeah.

294
00:27:47.212 --> 00:27:50.507
My whole life.
all I ever wanted was to have a baby

295
00:27:50.590 --> 00:27:53.009
and now because of you I can!

296
00:27:58.056 --> 00:28:00.225
God. now I just need to get healthy!

297
00:28:01.810 --> 00:28:03.812
Now I just need to get healthy

298
00:28:03.937 --> 00:28:06.940
so I can see the bugger
get into an Ivy League school.

299
00:28:08.441 --> 00:28:11.069
Of course you will. You will.

300
00:28:11.152 --> 00:28:15.282
Now you can tell that bastard ex-husband
of yours what he can do with his ethics.

301
00:28:19.703 --> 00:28:22.914
Because you're insufferable.
and you're mean.

302
00:28:23.707 --> 00:28:26.167
You asked me for the truth.
Mom. and that's...

303
00:28:26.251 --> 00:28:27.919
Ed.

304
00:28:28.920 --> 00:28:32.424
Let me call you later. OK?
OK. bye.

305
00:28:32.507 --> 00:28:35.802
- Hello. Jules. What's up?
- She's pregnant.

306
00:28:36.970 --> 00:28:39.973
- Excuse me?
- It worked. Rachel's pregnant.

307
00:28:43.184 --> 00:28:46.980
Jul... Juliet. that's...

308
00:28:47.063 --> 00:28:49.608
Wow.

309
00:28:49.691 --> 00:28:53.111
I need to see your labs.
We'll have to verify the data.

310
00:28:53.194 --> 00:28:54.905
No.

311
00:28:54.988 --> 00:28:57.240
I'm not interested in publishing. Ed.

312
00:28:58.241 --> 00:28:59.910
It's my sister.

313
00:28:59.993 --> 00:29:03.246
Fine. If you're not interested.
why are you concerned if...

314
00:29:23.308 --> 00:29:26.603
- You OK?
- Yeah.

315
00:29:26.686 --> 00:29:29.105
I just don't like blood too much.

316
00:29:29.648 --> 00:29:34.110
Well. then you probably
won't want to be looking at that.

317
00:29:37.781 --> 00:29:40.659
So. if you really
can get off the island.

318
00:29:40.742 --> 00:29:43.036
why didn't you just
take him to a facility?

319
00:29:43.119 --> 00:29:45.205
Why all this?

320
00:29:45.288 --> 00:29:48.249
Because ever since
the sky turned purple. we...

321
00:29:49.542 --> 00:29:53.338
- What the hell happened?
- I just nicked an artery.

322
00:29:53.755 --> 00:29:58.134
- Isn't that what you already did?
- Yeah. well. that was on purpose.

323
00:29:59.177 --> 00:30:00.387
Can you fix it?

324
00:30:01.721 --> 00:30:02.889
Damn it!

325
00:30:08.979 --> 00:30:10.522
- You got him?
- I got him.

326
00:30:12.816 --> 00:30:14.234
- Karl?
- Nice ride.

327
00:30:14.317 --> 00:30:17.028
- Karl. we're gonna go now.
- Help me.

328
00:30:17.112 --> 00:30:20.490
Can you stand? OK. Come on.

329
00:30:23.118 --> 00:30:26.871
So... you're the boss's daughter?

330
00:30:27.706 --> 00:30:31.209
I never saw that coming.
Let's go. Cheech.

331
00:30:32.043 --> 00:30:34.421
We're going for a little ride.

332
00:30:34.546 --> 00:30:36.881
- Careful.
- All right. Easy.

333
00:30:37.966 --> 00:30:40.093
I'm gonna put you in the boat.
all right?

334
00:30:41.052 --> 00:30:42.762
Wait. wait.

335
00:30:45.265 --> 00:30:46.433
- Are you OK?
- Danny.

336
00:30:46.516 --> 00:30:48.268
No. "Sawyer."

337
00:30:49.269 --> 00:30:51.187
Danny!

338
00:31:05.035 --> 00:31:07.495
- No!
- Danny!

339
00:31:24.929 --> 00:31:26.765
- What happened? Is he...?
- I can't see.

340
00:31:26.848 --> 00:31:28.975
- What?
- There's too much blood.

341
00:31:29.100 --> 00:31:30.769
All right. get over here.

342
00:31:30.852 --> 00:31:33.688
Tom. he is going to die
if you don't get over here now.

343
00:31:37.734 --> 00:31:39.277
Go.

344
00:31:40.862 --> 00:31:42.405
Get out of here.

345
00:31:44.074 --> 00:31:45.617
You heard the lady.

346
00:31:47.911 --> 00:31:50.288
- Let's go!
- Not you. Alex.

347
00:31:51.206 --> 00:31:53.792
- You're staying.
- Why?

348
00:31:53.875 --> 00:31:55.418
We both know your father.

349
00:31:55.502 --> 00:31:59.005
And the only way he'll let Karl live
is if you're here when he wakes up.

350
00:32:02.926 --> 00:32:04.761
I'm sorry. Alex.

351
00:32:13.520 --> 00:32:15.230
Hey. Alex.

352
00:32:15.313 --> 00:32:16.898
Hey.

353
00:32:17.607 --> 00:32:19.734
I missed you.

354
00:32:19.818 --> 00:32:22.862
I know. I missed you. too.

355
00:32:24.989 --> 00:32:27.534
You have to go away now...

356
00:32:27.659 --> 00:32:30.286
...but I'll see you real soon. OK?

357
00:32:30.954 --> 00:32:32.122
I love you.

358
00:32:38.002 --> 00:32:39.546
I have to go to sleep now.

359
00:32:52.183 --> 00:32:53.226
Wait.

360
00:32:55.228 --> 00:32:58.565
Easy. OK. Easy.

361
00:33:01.818 --> 00:33:03.486
Wait. wait...

362
00:33:03.570 --> 00:33:06.447
Keep it steady. damn it!
Hold it steady.

363
00:33:09.200 --> 00:33:11.077
<i>Jack. are you there?</i>

364
00:33:16.040 --> 00:33:19.544
All right. hold that up to me.
The walkie. Hold it up to me.

365
00:33:19.627 --> 00:33:22.046
- What about the suction?
- Just do it!

366
00:33:28.887 --> 00:33:30.597
Yeah. I'm here. Kate. You OK?

367
00:33:31.598 --> 00:33:35.393
Yeah. I... We've got a boat.
They're letting us go.

368
00:33:35.810 --> 00:33:36.978
Who's letting you go?

369
00:33:38.605 --> 00:33:40.398
The blonde woman.

370
00:33:40.481 --> 00:33:43.610
- So you're safe? You and Sawyer?
- Yes! Yeah.

371
00:33:43.943 --> 00:33:46.779
- Tell me.
- Tell you?

372
00:33:47.322 --> 00:33:50.241
On the beach. the day of the crash.
the story I told you.

373
00:33:50.325 --> 00:33:52.493
If you're safe. tell me.

374
00:33:52.619 --> 00:33:55.538
- You think this is the best time to...
- Shut up!

375
00:33:57.832 --> 00:34:01.544
You... were doing surgery on a girl.

376
00:34:04.088 --> 00:34:05.798
And you messed up.

377
00:34:05.882 --> 00:34:07.383
You made a mistake.

378
00:34:09.302 --> 00:34:13.598
<i>You tore something on her back
and all the nerves came loose.</i>

379
00:34:17.602 --> 00:34:19.646
And you said you were so afraid.

380
00:34:22.148 --> 00:34:24.025
<i>And you said the fear was so...</i>

381
00:34:26.194 --> 00:34:27.695
...real.

382
00:34:28.863 --> 00:34:30.907
And you didn't know what to do.

383
00:34:35.495 --> 00:34:37.330
So you counted to five.

384
00:34:40.833 --> 00:34:43.544
<i>And then you weren't afraid anymore.</i>

385
00:34:43.628 --> 00:34:46.756
<i>And then it was just gone.</i>

386
00:34:50.927 --> 00:34:52.428
And you fixed her.

387
00:34:53.763 --> 00:34:55.807
<i>You saved her.</i>

388
00:35:14.492 --> 00:35:16.828
I need you to make me a promise. Kate.

389
00:35:16.911 --> 00:35:18.204
Jack?

390
00:35:18.288 --> 00:35:21.165
Promise me that you'll never
come back here for me.

391
00:35:23.418 --> 00:35:24.711
Don't come back. Kate.

392
00:35:24.794 --> 00:35:27.547
- Jack. where are you? Please.
- Turn it off.

393
00:35:27.630 --> 00:35:31.217
<i>Jack? Jack! Please. where are...?</i>

394
00:35:42.895 --> 00:35:44.230
Trades are coming up.

395
00:35:46.941 --> 00:35:48.735
We gotta go.

396
00:35:52.238 --> 00:35:53.990
- Let's go.
- OK.

397
00:36:43.456 --> 00:36:45.792
We have some paperwork
we need you to sign...

398
00:36:46.584 --> 00:36:48.669
...but take your time.
there's no rush.

399
00:36:48.753 --> 00:36:50.296
Thank you.

400
00:37:52.984 --> 00:37:55.027
Were you able to remove the tumor?

401
00:37:58.614 --> 00:37:59.991
Yeah.

402
00:38:03.953 --> 00:38:06.914
You'll want to do a biopsy.
see if it's malignant.

403
00:38:12.378 --> 00:38:15.965
So. what now?
I just go back to my cell?

404
00:38:17.049 --> 00:38:19.343
Until they figure out
what to do with you.

405
00:38:23.890 --> 00:38:25.391
"They."

406
00:38:30.730 --> 00:38:31.898
What'd he say?

407
00:38:33.065 --> 00:38:35.443
- I'm sorry?
- Ben.

408
00:38:36.319 --> 00:38:38.946
What did he say that made you
want to save his life?

409
00:38:43.409 --> 00:38:45.369
It doesn't really matter what he said.

410
00:38:45.453 --> 00:38:46.746
It matters to me.

411
00:38:48.664 --> 00:38:52.251
After everything that
I have been put through...

412
00:38:53.711 --> 00:38:55.838
...you owe me an answer.

413
00:38:56.839 --> 00:38:58.925
And I wanna know what he said.

414
00:39:18.110 --> 00:39:19.153
Tissue?

415
00:39:20.112 --> 00:39:22.698
Thank you. Thanks.

416
00:39:33.501 --> 00:39:36.754
- Have we met?
- Hello. Dr. Burke.

417
00:39:39.215 --> 00:39:43.344
- Mr. Alpert?
- I'm... so sorry for your loss.

418
00:39:45.763 --> 00:39:47.390
What are you doing here?

419
00:39:47.473 --> 00:39:51.644
I saw what happened on the news and
your office said you were down here.

420
00:39:51.769 --> 00:39:54.981
I just wanted to express
my condolences in person

421
00:39:55.147 --> 00:39:56.774
before I went back to Portland.

422
00:39:56.857 --> 00:39:58.901
This is Ethan.
he's one of my colleagues.

423
00:39:58.985 --> 00:40:00.695
It's a pleasure to meet you.

424
00:40:07.743 --> 00:40:09.495
He was hit by a bus.

425
00:40:09.579 --> 00:40:12.665
I know. They say you were there
when it happened. It must...

426
00:40:12.748 --> 00:40:15.751
No. no. In our interview...

427
00:40:17.295 --> 00:40:21.007
I said... I said that I wanted...
I wanted him to get hit by a bus.

428
00:40:23.718 --> 00:40:26.846
Dr. Burke. I realize you're
a little shook up right now.

429
00:40:26.929 --> 00:40:29.307
but this is just a tragic accident.

430
00:40:29.390 --> 00:40:31.058
You can't blame yourself.

431
00:40:31.976 --> 00:40:34.186
I don't even remember you saying that.

432
00:40:39.317 --> 00:40:41.902
Why are you here. Mr. Alpert?

433
00:40:41.986 --> 00:40:45.615
Look... I know the timing is horrible.

434
00:40:45.698 --> 00:40:50.077
but we came because we're that serious
about getting you to come work with us.

435
00:40:53.289 --> 00:40:55.041
Just give us six months.

436
00:40:55.124 --> 00:40:58.711
If you need to. you can be back
before your sister gives birth.

437
00:41:00.921 --> 00:41:03.633
- How did you know that my...?
- We're very thorough

438
00:41:03.716 --> 00:41:05.509
in our recruitment process.

439
00:41:15.394 --> 00:41:18.564
- Can my sister come?
- Won't work. we're pretty remote.

440
00:41:18.648 --> 00:41:21.525
She wouldn't have access
to the treatment that she needs.

441
00:41:21.609 --> 00:41:24.570
But it's Portland.
There's plenty of clinics and...

442
00:41:24.737 --> 00:41:28.157
Well. actually...
We're not quite in Portland.

443
00:41:38.918 --> 00:41:40.836
I want to know what he said.

444
00:41:47.051 --> 00:41:50.763
I've been on this island
for three years. Jack.

445
00:41:50.846 --> 00:41:54.934
Three years. two months. and 28 days.

446
00:41:58.437 --> 00:42:00.147
He said that if I...

447
00:42:02.358 --> 00:42:03.984
...let him live...

448
00:42:05.945 --> 00:42:07.738
...and I helped you...

449
00:42:13.160 --> 00:42:15.913
...that he would finally
let me go home.

449
00:42:16.305 --> 00:43:16.498
